      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [ ¶ W ¶ e ¶ have pleasure in recording that the ¶  ¶ valuable fodder-grass, Panicum spectabile has ¶  ¶ at length reached the colony. We owe its introduction to our Government botanist, Baron ¶  ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">80.12.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Leader</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Letter not found. The text given here is from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'THE GARDEN.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>HORTICULTURAL NOTES.',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Leader<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>(Melbourne), 1 January 1881. On the assumption that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M's report<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>would have been<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>published<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>promptly when<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he made it,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is dated to 27 December 1880, the earliest<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>likely<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>date after the publication of the previous issue on 25 December 1880.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">W</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have pleasure in recording that the</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">valuable fodder-grass, Panicum spectabile has</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">at length reached the colony. We owe its introduction to our Government botanist, Baron</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">von Mueller, who, after considerable exertion,</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">has obtained a supply of th</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">seed through the</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">establishment of the Royal Botanic Garden,</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">K</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">w,</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 26 November 1880.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Seeds had been requested in M to J. Hooker, 28 May 1879.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and who authorises us to notify that he</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">will supply persons who desire to enter on its</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">propagation and culture, upon receipt of address with a twopenny stamp for postage, provided they have the means of raising it, and</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">their situations are such as might be suitable</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>f</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">or its growth, for, being a native of tropical</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Africa, it is not likely that it will be able to</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">endure more than a slight degree of frost. At</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">this season the seeds must have artificial treatment, and probably it will be also necessary to</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">keep th</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plants indoors until next spring</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">before trusting them in the open ground. The</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">seed did not appear, on inspection through the</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">microscope, to be in good condition, and there</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">f</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ore to make sure of its vegetating properties</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, t</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">he Baron had a trial made by having a portion sown in a pot in a greenhouse, where a</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">percentage— though rather small— had vegetated.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The seeds were propagated in a glass house 'at a friends place' (M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 1 January 1881 (in this edition as 81-01-01a). In the same letter M told Thiselton-Dyer:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'On careful examination I find however, that these flowers (and seeds) do not respond to the description of Pannicum spectabile. Possibly the Negros comprehend several species of Pannicum under the appellation Coapim.'</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>This grass must not be confounded</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">with another grass distributed in another</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">colony under the sam</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>name, and which</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">proved to be the well-known Andropogon</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">hal</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">pp</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">nsis,</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. by Richard Schomburgk;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 20 July 1878,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and M to R. Tate, 22 November 1879.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a coarse, though enduring plant,</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">useful in dry places, but a nuisance in arable</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">land on account of its creeping underground</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">stems being difficult to eradicate</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.]</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The article continues by giving details of its vernacular name in Angola, Coapim, and an account<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of its characteristics extracted from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B76.12.04.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Andropogon haleppensis</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Panicum spectabile</p>
         </div>
      </body>
